    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="115" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 18.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Messrs. Sinclair, Hamilton &amp; Co. to Earl
                                    Russell</persName>.—(Received February 8.)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>11 <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Helen’s
                                        Place,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">London, February</hi> 8,
                                1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord:</hi> Referring to our letter of 29th
                                January, as to the capture of the bark Saxon by the United States
                                steamer Vanderbilt, we have now the honor to inform your lordship
                                that the Saxon, at the time of capture, was at anchor within a mile
                                and a half of Penguin island, British territory.</p>
                <p>We have &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SINCLAIR, HAMILTON &amp; CO.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
